title: Fix URL, directory paths, and npred app.
body:
Hello, I like the app!

I changed the url in `withincor_tab.R` to an absolute path so that it wouldn't try to find the blog post as a relative path to the localhost.

The directory paths in the `source()` calls now match the git directories.

The `app.R` now has the progress bar parameter and body so that it will match `npred/app.R` and not throw an error due to not having a progress argument called.

title: Hyperlink DOIs to preferred resolver
body:
Hello :-)

The DOI Foundation [started recommending a new resolver](https://www.doi.org/doi_handbook/3_Resolution.html#3.8). While their URL change may be a bit ironic, it's now [encrypted](https://www.ssllabs.com/ssltest/analyze.html?d=doi.org) and the old `dx` subdomain is being redirected. So, there is no urgency here.

However, for consistency, this PRs suggests to update all static DOI links accordingly.

Cheers!

title: Add norm2beta function
body:
I added a function to convert a normal distribution to a beta distribution, along with tests (using [this math here](https://stats.stackexchange.com/a/12239/3025) to extract the shape parameters)

``` r
library(faux)

x <- rnorm(10000)
y <- norm2beta(x, 1, 3)
g <- ggplot2::ggplot() + ggplot2::geom_point(ggplot2::aes(x, y))
ggExtra::ggMarginal(g, type = "histogram")
```

![](https://i.imgur.com/CggQSxo.png)
